### Test Upload File API

### 1. Login to get token (replace with your actual credentials)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "your-email@example.com",
  "password": "your-password"
}

### 2. Upload a file (replace {token} with the token from login response)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/upload/file
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test-document.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-document.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Test file upload
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 3. Get all user files
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/upload/files
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 4. Get specific file info (replace {fileId} with actual file ID)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/upload/file/{fileId}
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 5. Download file (replace {fileId} with actual file ID)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/upload/file/{fileId}/download
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 6. Delete file (replace {fileId} with actual file ID)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/v1/upload/file/{fileId}
Authorization: Bearer {token}
